        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 11,
        "summary": "The stem of Jesse (Christ) will judge in righteousness\u2014The knowledge about God will cover the earth in the Millennium\u2014The Lord will raise an ensign and gather Israel\u2014Compare 2\u00a0Nephi 21.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And there shall come forth a rod out of the stem of Jesse, and a Branch shall grow out of his roots:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 21:1 (1\u201316); JS\u2014H 1:40.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 110:2; D&C 113:3 (1\u20136).",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 113:1 (1\u20132). TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Messiah; Jesus Christ, Prophecies about.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jesse was the father of David; reference is made to the royal Davidic genealogical line in which Jesus is eventually born. Micah 5:2; Heb. 7:14. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Davidic Descent of.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 23:5.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the spirit of the Lord shall rest upon him, the spirit of wisdom and understanding, the spirit of counsel and might, the spirit of knowledge and of the fear of the Lord;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of; Holy Ghost, Mission of.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Counsel.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And shall make him of quick understanding in the fear of the Lord: and he shall not judge after the sight of his eyes, neither reprove after the hearing of his ears:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Millennial Reign.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0by appearances and by hearsay. John 7:24. TG\u00a0Discernment, Spiritual; Sight.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But with righteousness shall he judge the poor, and reprove with equity for the meek of the earth: and he shall smite the earth with the rod of his mouth, and with the breath of his lips shall he slay the wicked.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 30:9 (8\u201315).",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of; Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0decide with equity. TG\u00a0Reproof.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meek.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 2:9; 2\u00a0Ne. 7:8.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 117
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 30:28.",
                        "start": 168,
                        "end": 174
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 139:19 (17\u201324); 2\u00a0Ne. 30:10 (10\u201311); D&C 63:33 (29\u201337).",
                        "start": 196,
                        "end": 200
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And righteousness shall be the girdle of his loins, and faithfulness the girdle of his reins.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 12:11; Isa. 59:17 (16\u201317); Eph. 6:14; D&C 27:16 (16\u201317).",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0waist.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The wolf also shall dwell with the lamb, and the leopard shall lie down with the kid; and the calf and the young lion and the fatling together; and a little child shall lead them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Nature, Earth.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the cow and the bear shall feed; their young ones shall lie down together: and the lion shall eat straw like the ox.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the sucking child shall play on the hole of the asp, and the weaned child shall put his hand on the cockatrice' den.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0the horned viper.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0another venomous serpent.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They shall not hurt nor destroy in all my holy mountain: for the earth shall be full of the knowledge of the Lord, as the waters cover the sea.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 60:18; D&C 101:26.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Zion.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hab. 2:14. TG\u00a0Earth, Renewal of.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Knowledge about; Knowledge; Millennium.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And in that day there shall be a root of Jesse, which shall stand for an ensign of the people; to it shall the Gentiles seek: and his rest shall be glorious.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the latter days. JS\u2014H 1:40.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 5:5; D&C 113:6 (5\u20136).",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Ensign.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0unto him.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gentiles; Israel, Mission of.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 119
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rest.",
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall come to pass in that day, that the Lord shall set his hand again the second time to recover the remnant of his people, which shall be left, from Assyria, and from Egypt, and from Pathros, and from Cush, and from Elam, and from Shinar, and from Hamath, and from the islands of the sea.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 137:6.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Gathering of; Israel, Restoration of; Restoration of the Gospel.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 104
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Ten Lost Tribes of.",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 116
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 10:20 (19\u201322); D&C 133:8.",
                        "start": 278,
                        "end": 285
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 877
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he shall set up an ensign for the nations, and shall assemble the outcasts of Israel, and gather together the dispersed of Judah from the four corners of the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Dispensations; Ensign; Kingdom of God, on Earth; Mission of Latter-day Saints.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The envy also of Ephraim shall depart, and the adversaries of Judah shall be cut off: Ephraim shall not envy Judah, and Judah shall not vex Ephraim.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "The tribes led by Judah and Ephraim were historically adversaries (after events of 1\u00a0Kgs. 12:16\u201320). In the latter days this enmity will be healed. TG\u00a0Envy.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 108
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Judah, People of.",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But they shall fly upon the shoulders of the Philistines toward the west; they shall spoil them of the east together: they shall lay their hand upon Edom and Moab; and the children of Ammon shall obey them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0fly down on the shoulder; i.e., attack the western slopes that were Philistine territory.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 10:8 (8\u20139).",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0together (i.e., Ephraim and Judah) they shall spoil.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord shall utterly destroy the tongue of the Egyptian sea; and with his mighty wind shall he shake his hand over the river, and shall smite it in the seven streams, and make men go over dryshod.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 10:11.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0facilitate the return, as in the days of Moses.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 182,
                        "end": 185
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And there shall be an highway for the remnant of his people, which shall be left, from Assyria; like as it was to Israel in the day that he came up out of the land of Egypt.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0a way, or road. See D&C 133:23\u201327.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 14:29; Isa. 19:23; 35:8 (8\u201310); 2\u00a0Ne. 21:16; D&C 133:27.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
